Description:
Ultimate Family Lifestyle Package
In response to COVID-19 this auction will be held online. Please contact us to obtain your registration link.
Inspections are by private appointment only.
Beautifully presented and ready for your family to move in, this solid brick four bedroom, two bathroom home offers relaxed living on an impressive allotment of approximately 835m2. Arched walkways open to multiple living spaces, including a spaciously sundrenched front lounge, versatile yet private dining room and fully equipped kitchen/meals fitted with stainless steel appliances, walk-in pantry, breakfast bar and filament lighting. Crafted for entertaining, the remarkable all-weather alfresco, fitted with electric blinds, features a suitable wood fire heater, while flowing into the landscaped backyard comprising garden shed, lockup double garage and gated undercover carport for multiple vehicles. The master bedroom boasts a convenient walk-through-robe to ensuite, as the central bathroom and separate toilet are flanked by the other bedrooms; two with built-in-robes. Further extras include polished hardwood floors, ducted heating, roomy laundry with backyard access, hallway storage, extensive driveway providing ample off-street-parking and pristine gardens. With something for everyone, it's moments from multiple schools, Keilor Central, community centres, parkland, Keilor Plains station and freeways.

Description:
Spacious Modern Townhouse in Central Location
Outstanding and hard to find in one of the West's most popular locations, this 30 square (Approx.) family sized residence of ample proportions in a prime location featuring quality in every detail.
Home comprises of 4 bedrooms, study, 4 bathrooms, 4 toilets, laundry, lock up garage. The generous kitchen is fitted with stone benches and walk in pantry, gas appliances, open plan living and dining which offers plenty of space leading to the undercover alfresco and low maintenance rear garden. The central position of the property benefits greatly from being less than 3 minutes to all key amenities and services including Alfrieda Street Shops, Library, Medical Clinics, Train Station Vic Uni and major arterial roads
Features: Ducted heating, cooling, large garage and much more

Description:
A New Benchmark in Low-Maintenance Luxury
Please register your interest in this property so that we can ensure you are included in the Virtual Auction and/or contacted in the event the property is going to be sold prior to the Virtual Auction 18 July at 12pm
*** This property is available for inspection by appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time ***
With its floorplan flexibility, premium inclusions and meticulous attention to detail, this spectacular new residence delivers a family lifestyle of unrivalled quality and exceptional urban convenience. Beautifully appointed, the home's truly opulent interior showcases four large bedrooms (master with fully-fitted walk-in robe) complemented by a luxurious ensuite with freestanding tub and two further bathrooms of equal elegance - all with recessed Geberit cisterns and floor-to-ceiling tiles. Adding to its family credentials is a lounge/retreat (upstairs) and wonderfully spacious open-plan living/dining area enhanced by a gourmet kitchen complete with butler's pantry and Franke appliances (dishwasher, oven, microwave, rangehood and 900mm gas cooktop). Heating and cooling throughout and high square-set ceilings across both levels, the home also includes a large laundry with ample linen cupboards, on-trend matt-black fittings, premium carpets and engineered timber floors, soft-close cabinetry, stone benchtops and double-glazed windows all-round. Large stacker doors reveal an al-fresco entertaining deck complete with mains-connected BBQ kitchen, plus a north-facing back garden with lawn area and internally-accessed garage via gated driveway (both remote-controlled). Other features include Paradox Security system with 5inch touch screen, sensors throughout the house and included remotes. The convenience of Matthews Avenue trams at the end of the street, it's also close to McNamara Avenue shops and cafes, St Christopher's Catholic Primary School, Westfield and Essendon Fields shopping centres, as well as easy access to the Tullamarine Freeway and Western Ring Road.
*** COVID-19 ANNOUNCEMENT ***
If you're attending a Private Appointment, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from our team members, and if requested wait outside until the property is ready for the appointment. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Light and Style on a Spacious Single Level!
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
So much more than meets the eye, this 4BR sixties' classic delivers an exceptional family lifestyle thanks to its expanded floorplan, quality enhancements throughout and terrific living/entertaining spaces both inside and out. Beyond the attractive rendered facade, discover a free-flowing interior comprising a large master bedroom with WIR and three further bedrooms (all with BIRs), together with a private ensuite and stylish family bathroom - both with floor-to-ceiling tiles. Enhancing its family credentials is a front lounge and adjoining dining room through to the spacious open-plan living/meals area accompanied by a contemporary kitchen with stone benchtops, tiled splashbacks, Smeg cooking appliances and Smeg dishwasher. Other stand-out features include ducted heating, evaporative cooling and two additional split-system air conditioners, solid hardwood floors (parquetry in the living area), alarm system and family-sized laundry. Completing the picture is an outside entertaining area, sunny north-facing backyard with lawn area, storage shed/workshop with power, plus front double carport and gated driveway for additional secure off-street parking. Immediate access to the best of inner Melbourne including the open spaces of Carlton Gardens, Brunswick Street cafes, bars and restaurants, shops and supermarkets, choice of tram routes, uni/hospital precincts, Parliament Station and the CBD.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance.
Thank you

Description:
Inspections Available By Appointment
Large Five Bedroom Home
Calder Real Estate is proud to represent the first homeowners of 88 Oleander Drive, St. Albans that have enjoyed calling this house home for some 40 years. Retro features distinguished by modern touches shine through the dimensions of this much loved brick veneer solid family home. The 1970s charmer is spread over a generous sized allotment of approximately 687sqm in a convenient locale with amenities including schools, shops, bus stops and train stations all a stones throw away. Comprising of grand veranda leading the wide hall entrance that seamlessly distributes the comfortable sunken lounge and dining thereon to the kitchen and family room featuring a built in bar. The sleeping quarters consist of 5 bedrooms with robes serviced by the central bathroom and separate WC. Includes, gas heating, air conditioning, ample storage, large driveway leading to oversized garage and workshop, second bathroom with W.C, rear veranda and more. Built on strip footings and concrete stumps making it a very solid home to last generations. Offering huge future potential to the home occupier wishing to occupy or investor, it is definitely a must see.

Set in a family friendly pocket of Kealba sits this perfect opportunity located nearby to quality primary and secondary schools, only a short distance to Overnewton Anglican College and St Pauls Catholic School, Kealba kindergarten, Calder Freeway, Western Ring Road, public transport, local shops, Green Gully Reserve, Maribyrnong river and so much more. Grasp this great opportunity to enter into the fast-growing market of Kealba.
Features Include:
Three spacious bedrooms all with built in robes
The kitchen is located perfectly to incorporate the meals area which leads out to a large outdoor entertaining area and sun room allowing ample space for gathering family and friends
Kitchen complete with ample cupboard space, electric cook top, electric over, dishwasher and double sink
Front formal lounge with heating furnace
Central bathroom with bathtub, shower and quality fittings
Evaporative cooling, garden shed, roller shutters, professional landscaped gardens and the list goes on
Double car garage
Side access is available
(Photo ID is Required at all Open For Inspections, Prior to Entry)
At YPA Caroline Springs Our Service Will Move You
DISCLAIMER: Every precaution has been taken to establish the accuracy of the above information but it does not constitute any representation by the vendor or agent/agency.

We are still conducting our business but with the safety & health of others and our team are the Highest Priority. Open for Inspections will consist of the following precautions for everyones safety, hand sanitizer will be available prior to entry and if requested will be required to be worn prior to entering.
We ask anyone that has recently returned from overseas and if you are unwell to ensure you please do not attend an open home or private inspection.
We thank everyone for their co-operation during this time and please Stay Safe.

Description:
ListedAS First Time on the Market
Theres a reason why the original owners have been here for 35 years
Tucked away in a quiet court with wonderful neighbours yet still walking distance to the best schools in Keilor Downs, this stunning home is full of charm and character.
From the vast formal lounge to the solid Blackwood timber kitchen flowing through to the rumpus, you will see the quality and craftsmanship this home entails. The rumpus features a bar so you can entertain inside or open the double sliding doors and let the party continue onto the decking and into the backyard.
Watch the kids play outside from the kitchen window, relax under the pergola in the summer time and buy that boat or caravan and park it safely via the drive through remote double garage.
There is something here for everyone.
Situated on a massive 675m2 land, with your choice of schools close by including Monmia Primary, St Mary MacKillop, Taylors Lakes Primary Secondary and within a short walk to Keilor Views Primary and Keilor Downs Secondary College.
Also within close proximity to Keilor Downs Shopping Centre, St Albans Leisure Centre and walk to multiple parks and playgrounds where your kids can play until the cows come home.

Be quick this potential packed home in a great location promises to be popular.

Description:
Family classic with space and potential.
In a quiet court location minutes from shopping centres, schools and freeways, this single level three bedroom brick home offers immediate comfort and terrific scope to make your renovation dream a reality (STCA). Set amidst established gardens, on land approximately 646sqm, the floor plan contains central living room warmed by floorboards and natural light streaming in through a large window. A generous dining area accompanies a well-equipped Tassie oak kitchen presenting stainless steel gas cook top, electric oven and dishwasher. All three bedrooms have built-in-robes and share a central bathroom, laundry and toilet. Outdoors you will find a chlorinated pool, garden shed and Activity/Pool room with Conara heater. Enjoys close proximity to parks, walking trails, St Peters Primary school and Milleara Shopping Centre.
Inspection by Appointment Only.

Description:
Cute, Cosy & No Body Corporate - Inspections by Private Appointment Only
Stylish with quality finishes throughout, this renovated street facing home offers a simple solution for those looking to avoid the hassles of renovation. Boasting 3 spacious bedrooms all equipped with built in robes, renovated sparkling central bathroom, gorgeous well-appointed kitchen with stainless steel appliances and wooden benchtop adjoined by the open plan living area. Additional features include security shutters, split system, beautiful decking at your doorstep overlooking the landscaped front yard, your own private driveway and plenty more. Conveniently located just moments away from Sunshine Avenue, Calder Freeway, Western Ring Road, St. Pauls Kealba Catholic School, parks and local buses. No expenses have been spared with this renovation, the only remaining thing is for you to call this place home. So don't miss out on this great opportunity and book your personal private inspection!
If you'd like to book an appointment call or email us today. Please note: No appointment, No entry.
COVID-19 Private property inspection rules
If you're attending a private inspection, you must only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so, have no reason to think that you have been contaminated and are not under any self-isolation conditions. There is a maximum of two people allowed to attend you must maintain social distancing requirements at all times. Please don't touch anything inside the property. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Hand sanitiser and disposable gloves will be provided for you before entering the home and we will insist that you use them. Thank you for your understanding.

Description:
Exceptionally Located and Full of Promise on 764m2!
Delivering unmistakable potential in one of St Albans favourite pockets. Families, investors and developers will not be able to look past this big brick home set on a large 764m2 approx. allotment.
The home features a wonderful three-bedroom floor-plan with a flexible option for an extra 4th bedroom, ensuite, study or rumpus. The big lounge room with fireplace is accompanied by a light filled meals area and an updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances, dishwasher and loads of storage space, leading to an enclosed sunroom with access to the huge backyard. Extra features include solid timber floorboards, ducted heating, evaporative cooling, roller shutters, double lock up garage, garden shed, green house and plenty of off-street parking.
There are plenty of options for buyers to explore, including renovating to taste or develop multiple dwellings (STCA). In an outstanding location close to Sacred Heart Primary School, Catholic Regional College St Albans, St Albans North Primary School, St Albans Primary School and Alfrieda Street Shopping Precinct. Central to St Albans Train Station and Keilor Plains Train Station.

Description:
Unlimited Potential In A Family Friendly Location
At approximately 605sqm of land situated in a peaceful neighbourhood with a super family friendly and community feel, number 7 Wingara is bursting with potential and opportunity. The current original weatherboard home, with timber floors throughout, features entry hallway, two bedrooms, each with BIR's, main providing ceiling fan, and a central bathroom with separate toilet. A comfortable lounge offering split system heating/cooling, adjoins the dining area and spacious kitchen, providing quality stainless steel appliances and plenty of cabinetry to deal with culinary clutter. A tiled sun room aside the laundry opens out to a terrific outdoor deck, screened and roofed for year round entertaining. With ducted heating, single garage plus additional off-street parking, garden shed and established garden, this is an outstanding chance to refurbish, renovate or redevelop (STCA) in a highly desirable suburb. Super convenient to Centreway shops and cafes, a range of quality schools (including PEGS) , local bus lines, Steele Creek nature trails, green spaces and freeway access , don't miss out on the opportunity to create an enviable lifestyle in a premier area.

Description:
Inspection by Private Appointment Only
FAMILY CLASS WITH SCOPE TO BE CREATIVE
Please ensure you also scroll through to the bottom of this ad to see our COVID-19 Property Inspection Policy!
Literally a few moments walk from Ginifer Station, Sunshine Hospital, Victoria University, schools, shopping and open parkland, this home offers dynamic lifestyle opportunities.
_natural light complements fresh paint & low maintenance floors
_lounge and kitchen/dining each set on a sensational scale
_three bedrooms (all with BIR), brilliantly sized and bright
_2-way central bathroom
_offering secure off-street parking
_reverse cycle air conditioning
_updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances
COVID-19 Property Inspection Policy
Public inspections are currently restricted to a maximum of 10 persons in the property at any one time (excluding those facilitating the inspection). There may be times in which you need to wait before you can enter the property and we appreciate your patience with this.
We take the health and well-being of our Team Members, Clients and the Community very seriously. Thats why weve developed a strict Condition of Entry Policy at our Inspections and Auctions, as follows:
_Social distancing of at least 1.5 mtrs from others
_No touching of any item or surface within the property
_Practicing good hygiene (with sanitisers, gloves and masks where available)
If you fall into any of the below categories, please just stay at home and have a rest!
_Are unwell with any flu-like symptoms
_Have been tested for and are awaiting results or have been confirmed positive for Covid-19
_Have been in contact with anybody who is being tested for or has been confirmed to have or have had Covid-19
_Have returned from overseas in the past 14 days
If you fall into these categories, rest assured, we are more than happy to give you a virtual property tour or make other arrangements instead. Just contact us to make arrangements!
